summary: SummaryL'Oréal Infallible Skin Ink 2-in-1 Foundation Concealer has up to 48H wear yet is light as ink. Transfer-resistant, waterproof, sweat proof, and humidity proof.
details: DetailsFeaturesThe future of makeup - Infallible Skin Ink 2-in-1 Foundation Concealer. Up to 48H of wear yet light as ink, lasts until you decide to remove.Skin Ink evens like a foundation and covers like a concealer. Designed to be customized with buildable longwear where you need it in a soft matte finish that doesn't cake and doesn't crease.L'Oréal's patented formula flexes to move with your skin. It is so lightweight it feels undetectable on skin while lasting until you decide to remove.Up to 48H wear that's transfer resistant, waterproof, sweat proof, and humidity proof.Grips so hard you don't need a primer. Self-setting.Item 2640586How To UsePrep skin with a hydrating moisturizer or serum.Shake bottle.Working in small sections of the face, apply then immediately blend with a brush.Lasts until you decide to removeRemove by double cleansing with an oil based product followed by a water based cleanse.IngredientsIsododecane, Hexyl/Succinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Trimethylsiloxysilicate/Dimethiconol Crosspolymer, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Nylon-611/Dimethicone Copolymer, Triethoxysilylethyl Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate, Propylene Carbonate, Alcohol Denat., Alumina, Phenoxyethanol, Silica. May Contain: CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, CI 77007 / Ultramarines].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsShipping Restrictions : This item cannot be shipped via air.
how_to_use: Prep skin with a hydrating moisturizer or serum.Shake bottle.Working in small sections of the face, apply then immediately blend with a brush.Lasts until you decide to removeRemove by double cleansing with an oil based product followed by a water based cleanse.

reviews.headline: after years I have found my perfect foundation
reviews.comments: Ok so I NEVER write reviews, but I feel like I have to because I dont want this product to be discontinued anytime soon. I have a long history of trying foundations and hating them and how they sit on my skin. Product never sits on my nose, breaks down all over my forehead within an couple hours, and sinks into the lines under my eyes horribly. This product solves ALL of those problems for me. It actually sits on my nose and stays put!  Same with my forehead. It doesnt settle into my under eyes at all. Not to mention i wore it for 7 hours, and 4 of those hours I was sweaty being active and it didn't come off my face or break apart at all! This foundation is my first ever 10/10. And I've been into make now for over 10 years. Please never get rid of this foundation!!

faceoff_positive.comments:
L'Oréal Paris Skin Ink (often referred to as a "tinted serum" or "super-lightweight foundation")
This product is designed to be extremely lightweight, offering a "barely-there" feel with some coverage to unify the complexion. It's part of L'Oréal's ongoing push into more natural-looking, skincare-infused makeup.
Key Features and Benefits (based on product descriptions and user reviews):
 * Ultra-Lightweight, Water-Thin Texture: This is the most defining characteristic. It's often described as feeling like "water" or "ink" on the skin, hence the name. It's designed to be imperceptible once applied.
 * "No Makeup" Makeup Look: It provides very sheer to light coverage, aiming to even out skin tone, blur imperfections, and give a natural, healthy appearance without masking the skin. It lets your natural skin show through.
 * Non-Comedogenic: Often formulated not to clog pores, making it suitable for various skin types, including those prone to breakouts.
 * Comfortable Wear: Due to its light texture, it's generally very comfortable to wear throughout the day, feeling like nothing is on your skin.
 * Easy Application: Can be applied with fingers, a brush, or a sponge. Its thin consistency often makes it blend seamlessly.
 * Natural Finish: Typically provides a natural, often slightly dewy or satin-matte finish, depending on skin type and subsequent powder use.
 * Good for Summer or Humid Climates: Its lightweight nature makes it a popular choice for warmer weather when heavy foundations can feel uncomfortable.
Common Praises from Reviews:
 * Feels like nothing: Users consistently rave about how light and breathable it feels on the skin.
 * Natural perfection: It achieves that coveted "your skin but better" look, making skin look healthier and more even without appearing
faceoff_positive.headline: I highly recommend this product!

faceoff_negative.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really wanted to like this product, but it just didn't work for me. From the start, the texture felt off, very thin and watery, but somehow also drying at the same time. It didn't sit well on my skin and seemed to crack or separate as it dried, which made my skin look worse, not better.
The scent also threw me off. It has a strong chemical smell that was hard to ignore. I usually don't mind light or even unscented products, but this one just didn't smell good at all.
Shade was pretty good. For me it's hard to find shades bc I'm olive undertone this one was pretty good. I have the warm 100.
That said, I'll give credit where it's due. The packaging is super cute and the applicator is actually really nice. It gives you control and applies the product smoothly. Unfortunately, the formula itself just didn't live up to the rest.
